slapt-get: slapt-get (an Apt-like front-end to Slackware's pkgtools)
slapt-get:
slapt-get: slapt-get is an apt-like front-end to Slackware's pkgtools.
slapt-get: It allows you to install/upgrade/uninstall packages using 
slapt-get: "repositories" (very similar to the way Debian does it). 
slapt-get:  
slapt-get: slapt-get is required by GSB for some of the installer functions.
slapt-get:
slapt-get: slapt-get was written by the amazing Jason Woodward:
slapt-get:   <http://software.jaos.org>
slapt-get:
